        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: native SwiftUI Crabbox iOS app (crabbox.sh client + on-device/sandbox LLM + islo)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nEvolves the `mobile/` surface from the Expo WebView prototype into a **genuinely native SwiftUI iOS app** for `crabbox.sh`, with an on-device/sandbox **LLM assistant** and the ability to **trigger islo sandboxes from the phone**. No web wrapper, no Expo, no third‑party runtime (except MLX for on‑device inference).\n\n## Architecture\n\nOne portable Swift brain, three native tabs:\n\n- **`CrabboxKit`** (pure Swift, builds on macOS **and** Linux, unit‑tested): coordinator‑URL normalization, the HTTPS‑only navigation/whitelist policy, the `reduce()` app state machine, and the LLM/sandbox clients — `OllamaClient`, `SandboxEngine`, `IsloClient`, `CoordinatorClient`, and the `SandboxProvisioner` abstraction (crabbox.sh‑primary + optional direct islo.dev).\n- **SwiftUI app** — **Portal** (`WKWebView` of crabbox.sh: native chrome, OAuth‑persisting `WKWebsiteDataStore`, HTTPS‑only ATS, origin allow‑list, external‑scheme routing, pull‑to‑refresh, Guideline‑4.2 chrome), **Assistant** (engine‑agnostic chat over **on‑device MLX**, **sandbox Ollama**, or **Apple Foundation Models**), **Sandboxes** (list/create/stop + \"launch an LLM sandbox\" and chat with it).\n- **`crabbox-sim`** — headless e2e that drives the *exact* `reduce()` the app uses through **17 scenarios / 13 invariants** (18 checks, 0 violations), plus a tiny‑LLM (Ollama `qwen2.5:0.5b`) agentic driver with a deterministic fallback. This is what runs on an islo sandbox.\n- **`crabbox-mac`** — a native `WKWebView` preview harness so the portal can be exercised on a Mac with only the Command Line Tools.\n\n## Sandboxes & islo\n\nThe phone provisions sandboxes through `SandboxProvisioner`. crabbox.sh (the coordinator) is the primary, key‑less path; **islo.dev** is the optional direct provider (islo is brokerless by Crabbox design) — the user saves an islo key in the Keychain and the app talks to `api.islo.dev` directly, then chats with Ollama on the leased box.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `swift build` + `swift test` + `swift run crabbox-sim` — green locally (macOS) and in CI (Linux + macOS).\n- `xcodegen generate` produces a valid `Crabbox.xcodeproj`; CI builds the iOS app unsigned (`xcodebuild`, `CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO`).\n- On‑device MLX is gated behind `#if canImport(MLXLLM)` and opt‑in in `project.yml`, so the app builds without the package (the on‑device engine reports unavailable until enabled in Xcode).\n\n## Distribution\n\nFree provisioning (try today), TestFlight/App Store (paid Apple account). See `mobile/docs/distribution.md`.\n",
